Not saying I disagree with you, but what is your plan to deal with medication non-compliant individuals? Institutionalization is neat, but there are civil liberties involved and people cant be held without cause. They go in. Stabilize, release, regress. It's not necessarily about community resources either. Many people absolutely hate how anti-psychotic medication makes them feel and refuse to take it outside of the institution. Or they go back on self medicating.
